                explanation: 'LCP is the render time of the largest content element. To optimize: (1) `<link rel="preload">` in `<head>` starts downloading before the browser discovers the `<img>` tag, (2) WebP/AVIF is 30-50% smaller than JPEG for the same quality, (3) `fetchpriority="high"` tells the browser this is the most important resource to load. NEVER use `loading="lazy"` on above-the-fold images — it delays LCP further.',
