                correctAnswer: 'Passwords in URLs appear in: browser history, server access logs, proxy logs, Referer headers sent to third-party scripts, and are visible to anyone looking over the user\'s shoulder. Fix: always use `method="POST"` for credentials, and ensure HTTPS',
                explanation: 'GET requests expose credentials in: (1) Browser history (sharable, sync\'d across devices), (2) Web server access logs (often stored for months), (3) CDN/reverse proxy logs, (4) Referer headers in HTTP requests to any third-party analytics or CDN loaded on the next page. POST + HTTPS keeps credentials in the encrypted request body with no URL exposure. This is a fundamental web security requirement.',
