                explanation: 'Stacking contexts are created by: `position` + `z-index` (non-auto), `opacity < 1`, `transform`, `filter`, `isolation: isolate`, etc. z-index comparisons are relative within a stacking context. If the modal\'s parent has `opacity: 0.99` (creating a context), the modal\'s z-index only competes within that context — the parent context then competes against the dropdown\'s context. Debug with browser DevTools → Layers panel.',
