                correctAnswer: 'Changing `left` or `margin` triggers Layout (reflow), then Paint, then Composite — expensive and causes jank. `transform` and `opacity` ONLY trigger the Composite step, which runs on the GPU thread without blocking the main thread',
                explanation: 'The browser rendering pipeline: Layout (calculate positions) → Paint (draw pixels) → Composite (combine layers). `left`/`margin` changes force the browser to recalculate layout for the element AND potentially its neighbors. `transform` bypasses Layout and Paint entirely — it\'s handled by the GPU compositor thread even when the main thread is busy. This is why CSS transform animations are silky smooth at 60fps while positional animations can stutter.',
