                correctAnswer: 'NoSQL document database',
                explanation: 'MongoDB stores data as flexible JSON-like documents (BSON). Unlike relational databases, there are no fixed schemas — each document in a collection can have different fields. MongoDB is horizontally scalable and excels at hierarchical/nested data structures. NoSQL does not mean "no querying" — MongoDB has a powerful query language.',
