                explanation: 'Documents are the basic unit of data in MongoDB, stored in BSON (Binary JSON) format. They can have nested objects and arrays. Example: `{ "_id": ObjectId("..."), "name": "Alice", "address": { "city": "Mumbai" }, "tags": ["admin", "user"] }`. Maximum document size: 16MB.',
