                correctAnswer: 'A group of related documents — equivalent to a table in SQL',
                explanation: 'Collections hold documents of (usually) similar purpose — e.g., a `users` collection, an `orders` collection. Unlike SQL tables, collections don\'t enforce a schema by default. You can add schema validation rules using `$jsonSchema` if needed. Collections are created automatically when you first insert a document.',
