                correctAnswer: 'A unique identifier automatically added to every document (ObjectId by default)',
                explanation: 'MongoDB automatically creates `_id` if not provided. The default type is `ObjectId` — a 12-byte value encoding timestamp, machine ID, process ID, and a counter — globally unique and sortable by creation time. You can override `_id` with your own value (string, UUID, etc.) as long as it\'s unique within the collection.',
