                correctAnswer: 'Performs a left outer join with another collection, adding matched documents as an array field',
                explanation: '`$lookup` joins collections server-side. Example: join `orders` with `products` on `productId`. The matched documents from the foreign collection are added as an array. Unlike SQL JOINs, `$lookup` runs in the pipeline — result arrays can be large if not filtered. Embedding related data (denormalization) is often preferred in MongoDB to avoid expensive lookups.',
