                correctAnswer: 'Embed when data is accessed together and has bounded size (1:1, 1:few); reference when data grows unboundedly or is accessed independently (1:many with large arrays)',
                explanation: 'Rule of thumb: "If you always load A with B, embed B in A." Example: embed user address (always loaded with user, bounded size). Reference: user → orders (orders can grow to thousands, often accessed independently). Embedded docs are fetched atomically in one read. References require $lookup or application-side joins (two queries). The 16MB document limit also constrains embedding.',
