                explanation: 'Rebase rewrites commit SHAs. When your teammate pulls, Git sees both old and new commits as unique (different SHAs, same content) and merges them, creating duplicate commits. Fix for affected teammates: `git fetch && git reset --hard origin/feature`. Prevention: only rebase LOCAL-ONLY commits. For shared branches, use merge. GitHub\'s "squash and merge" does this safely server-side.',
