                correctAnswer: 'DaemonSet',
                explanation: 'A DaemonSet ensures exactly one Pod runs on every node (or a subset via node selectors). When nodes are added, the Pod is automatically scheduled there; when nodes are removed, the Pod is garbage collected. Perfect for infrastructure-level agents: Fluentd, Prometheus node-exporter, CNI plugins.',
