                explanation: 'Ingress defines HTTP routing rules (host-based or path-based) pointing to Services. An Ingress controller (nginx, Traefik, AWS ALB) implements these rules. This avoids creating a LoadBalancer per Service. Example: `api.example.com` → api-service, `example.com/app` → frontend-service.',
