                explanation: 'A PersistentVolume (PV) is a piece of cluster storage (cloud disk, NFS, etc). A PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC) is a request for storage that binds to a PV. Pods mount PVCs, not PVs directly. StorageClasses enable dynamic provisioning — the PV is created automatically when a PVC is submitted. `emptyDir` is ephemeral and dies with the Pod.',
