                correctAnswer: 'StatefulSet — it gives Pods stable network identities, ordered startup/shutdown, and each Pod gets its own PVC via volumeClaimTemplates',
                explanation: 'StatefulSets are designed for stateful apps. Key guarantees: (1) stable Pod names: pod-0, pod-1, pod-2; (2) ordered, graceful startup/shutdown — pod-1 only starts after pod-0 is Ready; (3) each Pod gets its own PVC (not shared) via `volumeClaimTemplates`; (4) headless Service for direct Pod DNS (pod-0.service.ns.svc.cluster.local). Critical for databases like MongoDB, Cassandra, etcd.',
