                correctAnswer: 'Gives owner read/write/execute, group and others read/execute permissions',
                explanation: 'Permissions in Linux are 3 octal digits: owner, group, others. Each digit: 4=read (r), 2=write (w), 1=execute (x). 7=rwx (4+2+1), 5=rx (4+1). So 755: owner has rwx, group has r-x, others have r-x. This is typical for executable scripts.',
