                explanation: 'The pipe `|` connects commands. `cat file.txt | grep "error" | wc -l` counts error lines: cat outputs the file, grep filters for "error", wc -l counts lines. This is the Unix philosophy: small tools that do one thing well, composed together via pipes.',
