                explanation: 'Velocity is a measure of the amount of work (in story points, user stories, or hours) a team completes in a sprint. It is calculated by averaging completed story points across recent sprints. Velocity is used for forecasting: if a team averages 40 points per sprint and a release requires 160 points, expect ~4 sprints. Velocity is a team-specific planning tool, NOT a measure of productivity or a metric to compare across teams.',
                points: 1,
                orderIndex: 4,
