                explanation: 'The Definition of Done (DoD) is a checklist agreed upon by the whole team that defines what "complete" means for any work item. Typical DoD includes: code written, unit tests passing, code reviewed, integrated into main branch, deployed to staging, documentation updated, acceptance criteria met. The DoD ensures consistent quality and prevents "90% done" items. It is different from Acceptance Criteria — DoD applies to ALL stories; Acceptance Criteria are story-specific.',
