                explanation: 'Scaling Agile introduces coordination problems that single-team Scrum doesn\'t address. Major frameworks: **SAFe**: PI Planning (typically 2 days, all teams together) aligns 5–12 teams on 8–12 week roadmaps, identifies cross-team dependencies, and surfaces risks. Teams then run synchronized sprints. **LeSS (Large-Scale Scrum)**: Simpler — one Product Backlog, one Product Owner, multiple Scrum teams with shared Sprint Review and Retrospective. **Nexus**: Scrum@Scale — adds an integration team. For the described problems (duplicate work + conflicting changes + inconsistent DoD), SAFe\'s explicit dependency mapping and PI Planning, combined with a shared Program Backlog and Agile Release Train (ART) concept, most directly address coordination. LeSS with a unified DoD is also strong.',
