                explanation: 'Frames (press F) are the fundamental containers in Figma. Unlike Groups, Frames: (1) Have defined dimensions and can clip content; (2) Support Auto Layout, constraints, and prototype connections; (3) Can be nested (Frames within Frames); (4) Are used to represent screens, sections, or UI components. Device presets (iPhone, iPad, Desktop) are pre-sized frames. Frames show their name in the left panel and can be targeted directly in prototypes. Groups (⌘G) are simpler — they just bundle layers together without the layout and constraint features.',
