                correctAnswer: 'Design mode is where you create and style elements; Prototype mode is where you define interactions and flows between frames',
                explanation: 'Figma has two primary modes in the right panel: **Design mode**: Edit visual properties — colors, typography, layout, effects, component properties. This is where you build the design. **Prototype mode**: Define interactions — click connections between frames, transition animations (ease, spring, dissolve), scrolling behavior, overlays, and smart animate. Prototype mode turns static designs into interactive clickable flows. The **Dev mode** (third option) shows code-ready specs for developers: CSS properties, measurements, assets. You switch between modes using the tabs at the top of the right panel.',
