                correctAnswer: 'A saved, reusable design property (color, text, effect, or grid) that can be applied to multiple elements',
                explanation: 'Styles are named, reusable design tokens: (1) **Color Styles**: brand colors — Primary Blue (#2563EB), Background (#F8FAFC); (2) **Text Styles**: typography — Heading/H1, Body/Regular, Caption; (3) **Effect Styles**: shadows, blurs — Card Shadow, Focus Ring; (4) **Grid Styles**: layout grids — 12-column, 8px spacing. When you update a Style, ALL elements using it update simultaneously — like CSS variables. Styles are the predecessor to Variables (Figma 2023+). Variables are more powerful (modes/themes), but Styles remain widely used for typography and effects.',
