                correctAnswer: 'An online whiteboarding and diagramming tool by Figma for brainstorming, workshops, and flow charts',
                explanation: 'FigJam is Figma\'s online whiteboard product (separate from the design tool). Use cases: (1) Team brainstorming and mind mapping; (2) User journey mapping; (3) Affinity diagrams and post-it clustering; (4) Flowcharts and process diagrams; (5) Remote workshop facilitation (voting, timers, reactions); (6) Architecture diagrams. Key features: sticky notes, shapes, connectors, stamps, cursor chat. FigJam files (.jam) are separate from Figma design files (.fig). Teams use FigJam for early discovery/ideation and Figma for actual UI design. It integrates with Jira, Notion, and other tools.',
