                questionText: 'Your company has a design system library with 200 components shared across 6 product teams. After a brand refresh, the design system team updated all components in the library. Two weeks later, you discover that 3 product teams are still using the old designs because their files show "X updates available" notifications that were ignored, and some designers detached components to make local tweaks. What is the BEST long-term governance strategy?',
