                correctAnswer: 'Establish a versioned component library with a migration guide, a Design System Slack channel for update announcements, a deprecation period policy, and clear guidelines prohibiting component detaching in favor of component overrides or proposing new variants',
                explanation: 'This is a design system governance problem. Technical solutions alone fail without process: (1) **Versioning**: Major changes (brand refresh) need a migration guide — "what changed, how to update your file, timeline"; (2) **Communication**: Slack channel + changelog so teams aren\'t surprised by "X updates available"; (3) **Deprecation policy**: Old components stay live for N weeks with "deprecated" label — teams have time to migrate; (4) **No detaching rule**: Detaching severs the link permanently — the policy should require proposing new variants or overrides instead. When a designer needs something the component doesn\'t support, they open a PR to the design system, not detach locally; (5) **Adoption tracking**: The design system team should audit which files have pending updates.',
