                correctAnswer: 'Ask them to document the specific requirements, open a design system contribution request, build a local version temporarily with a note to reconcile later, and commit to a timeline for the official component',
                explanation: 'This is the classic "design system bottleneck" problem. The right balance: (1) **Don\'t block product teams indefinitely** — they have shipping deadlines and will detach anyway; (2) **Don\'t encourage detaching without a plan** — it creates permanent divergence; (3) **Contribution model**: The product team builds a local version WITH documentation of their solution → the DS team reviews it → it gets promoted to the library with refinements. This is how most mature design systems grow. Key process: the local version is marked "temporary — pending DS adoption" in the Figma file; a Jira ticket tracks the DS work; the DS team commits to a timeline (e.g., 2 sprints). The product team\'s implementation becomes the seed for the official component.',
