                correctAnswer: 'Header.Payload.Signature — user ID is stored in the payload as a claim (e.g., "sub" or "userId")',
                explanation: 'JWT structure: **Header** (base64url): `{"alg": "HS256", "typ": "JWT"}` — algorithm and token type; **Payload** (base64url): claims — `{"sub": "user_123", "email": "alice@example.com", "role": "admin", "iat": 1234567890, "exp": 1234571490}`; **Signature**: HMAC-SHA256(base64url(header) + "." + base64url(payload), SECRET_KEY) — verifies integrity. IMPORTANT: The payload is base64url-encoded, NOT encrypted. Anyone can decode it — never put passwords or sensitive data in JWT. The signature prevents tampering. Standard claims: "sub" (subject/user ID), "iat" (issued at), "exp" (expiration), "iss" (issuer). Verify the signature server-side before trusting the payload.',
