                questionText: 'Your Next.js blog uses ISR with `revalidate: 3600` (1 hour). A critical article has a factual error and the editor publishes a correction in the CMS. The error will remain live for up to 1 hour, causing reputational damage. What is the BEST architecture to allow immediate content updates while retaining ISR performance benefits?',
