                explanation: 'Regularization adds a penalty to the loss to discourage large weights, preventing overfitting: **L1 (Lasso)**: Loss + λ∑|wᵢ|. The absolute value penalty creates sparse models — some weights become exactly 0. Effectively performs automatic feature selection. Good when you suspect many features are irrelevant. **L2 (Ridge)**: Loss + λ∑wᵢ². The squared penalty distributes shrinkage evenly — weights become small but rarely zero. Better when all features are somewhat relevant. **Elastic Net**: combines L1 and L2. The λ (lambda) hyperparameter controls regularization strength — larger λ = more regularization = simpler model. Both prevent overfitting by reducing model complexity.',
