                explanation: 'This is **data drift / concept drift** — one of the most common real-world ML failures. Types: **Data drift (covariate shift)**: input feature distribution changes (e.g., different customer demographics in 2024); **Concept drift**: the relationship P(Y|X) changes (e.g., what predicts default changed due to inflation, new regulations). For time-series financial data: **Never use random train/test split** — it leaks future data into training. Use **walk-forward validation** (train on 2020, validate on 2021; train on 2020-21, validate on 2022). Mitigations: (1) Retrain monthly/quarterly on recent data; (2) Monitor feature distributions and prediction distributions in production (PSI — Population Stability Index); (3) Set up alerts when AUC degrades; (4) Consider ensemble with recent data weighted higher. The 18-point AUC drop is severe — indicates both drift AND temporal leakage in the original validation approach.',
