                correctAnswer: 'Processing grid-structured data like images by learning spatial hierarchies of features via convolutional filters',
                explanation: 'CNNs exploit the spatial structure of images. Key components: **Convolutional layer**: applies learned filters (kernels) that slide across the image detecting local features (edges, textures, patterns); **Pooling layer** (MaxPool): reduces spatial dimensions, provides translation invariance; **Fully connected layer**: final classification. Key insight: **parameter sharing** — a filter learned for one part of the image works everywhere (unlike fully connected layers). This makes CNNs much more parameter-efficient than MLPs for images. Applications: image classification, object detection (YOLO, Faster R-CNN), segmentation, medical imaging.',
                points: 1,
