                explanation: '`GridSearchCV` performs an exhaustive search over all specified parameter combinations, which grows exponentially (e.g. 5 depths × 4 estimators × 3 features × 5 folds = 300 fits). `RandomizedSearchCV` samples a user-specified number of combinations (`n_iter`). Research (Bergstra & Bengio) shows that randomized search is highly effective because not all hyperparameters are equally important. It finds near-optimal parameters in a fraction of the time, making it much more practical for large search spaces and big datasets.',
