                explanation: 'When the target variable (y) is highly skewed, regression models (especially linear ones) violate the homoscedasticity assumption, leading to poor predictions. Transforming the target using `np.log1p` during training and applying `np.expm1` to predictions resolves this. **`TransformedTargetRegressor`** automates this completely. It wraps a base estimator (e.g. Ridge) and a transformer (e.g., `PowerTransformer` or custom functions `func=np.log1p, inverse_func=np.expm1`). During `.fit(X, y)`, it fits the transformer on `y`, transforms it, and fits the regressor. During `.predict(X)`, it predicts the transformed values and automatically runs them through the inverse transformation, preventing manual prediction scaling bugs.',
