                explanation: 'Traditional word-level tokenizers replace any word not seen during training with a special `<UNK>` (unknown) token. This loses all meaning (e.g. misspelling "running" as "runnning" becomes `<UNK>`). **Subword tokenizers** (BPE, WordPiece, SentencePiece) build a vocabulary of characters and common subwords. When they encounter an unseen word like "runnning", they break it down into familiar parts (e.g., "run", "##n", "##ing"). This completely eliminates the OOV problem, significantly reduces vocabulary size (from millions to ~30k), and allows the model to process neologisms, spelling errors, and compound words intelligently.',
