                explanation: '**Anchor-based** models (Faster R-CNN, RetinaNet) use sliding windows with pre-defined bounding boxes (anchors) of various sizes and aspect ratios. The network predicts offsets relative to these anchors. The disadvantage: anchors require extensive manual tuning (matching datasets) and introduce massive computational redundancy. **Anchor-free** models (YOLOv8, FCOS, CenterNet) predict bounding boxes directly at each pixel location (as distance to boundaries or from a center keypoint). This eliminates the anchor-tuning hyperparameter, drastically simplifies the model (reducing head complexity), speeds up training/inference, and naturally handles objects of highly varying scales.',
