                explanation: 'The **receptive field** defines how much of the original input image a neuron can "see". A single 3x3 conv layer has a 3x3 receptive field. Stacking a second 3x3 layer on top of it gives the top neurons a **5x5 receptive field** over the original input. Benefits of stacking two 3x3s over a single 5x5: (1) **Parameter efficiency**: a single 5x5 kernel has $5 \\times 5 = 25$ weights (per channel). Two 3x3 kernels have $2 \\times (3 \\times 3) = 18$ weights. That is a **28% reduction** in parameters; (2) **More representation capacity**: stacking two layers allows you to insert two separate non-linear activations (e.g. ReLU) instead of one, making the network significantly more expressive.',
