                explanation: '**RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** is the optimal architecture for this scenario. Why: (1) **Up-to-date**: updating the Vector DB is near-instantaneous and cheap (simply add/update text vectors), whereas fine-tuning a 70B model weekly is extremely expensive, slow, and computationally intensive; (2) **Accuracy**: RAG provides the LLM with the exact source text, dramatically reducing hallucinations by forcing the model to rely only on the retrieved facts; (3) **Traceability**: RAG allows you to return citations (e.g., "According to Section 4.2 of Policy X...") so the user can verify the answer. Fine-tuning does not guarantee fact retrieval and can still hallucinate outdated weights. Prompting with *all* documents fails due to context window limits, cost, and high attention-loss (needle-in-a-haystack problem).',
