                correctAnswer: 'Implement a rolling history buffer combined with semantic summarization: maintain the system prompt and a sliding window of the last 10 messages, and summarize older conversation history into a running summary paragraph placed at the top of the context window.',
                explanation: 'A naive approach of letting conversation accumulate will crash the API once the tokens exceed the model\'s context limit (e.g. 8k). Simply slicing off older messages (sliding window only) leads to a rapid loss of context, where the model forgets what the user said 15 minutes ago. The industry standard is **summarized history management**: (1) The system prompt (defining behavior) is locked at the top; (2) The most recent $N$ messages (e.g., last 10) are retained in full to maintain local conversational flow; (3) All historical messages older than $N$ are periodically passed to a background LLM call that updates a concise "running summary" of key facts, which is inserted right after the system prompt. This keeps VRAM usage low and stable while preserving long-term conversational memory.',
