                questionText: 'You are deploying a 70-billion parameter Large Language Model (Llama-3-70B) in production. Your API must serve 50 concurrent users with low latency (<50ms Time-to-First-Token and >30 tokens/second/user). The standard model weights alone require 140GB in float16. What production serving architecture and optimization techniques will achieve this under VRAM and compute constraints?',
                questionType: 'mcq',
