                    'Load the 140GB model in float16 onto a single 80GB NVIDIA A100 GPU and use native PyTorch model.predict() inside an asynchronous FastAPI thread pool.',
                    'Deploy the model across two 80GB NVIDIA A100 GPUs using Tensor Parallelism (splitting matrix multiplications). Use a high-performance serving framework (like vLLM) that implements PagedAttention to prevent KV cache fragmentation, continuous batching (iteration-level scheduling) to group concurrent requests, and AWQ/GPTQ 4-bit weight quantization to reduce VRAM requirements to ~40GB.',
                    'Export the model to ONNX format and run CPU inference on a cluster of 128-core machines behind a round-robin load balancer.',
                    'Set the context window of the model to exactly 64 tokens, and disable the self-attention mechanism to save VRAM.'
