                questionText: 'When building a code-generation assistant or a structured database-query generator (e.g., text-to-SQL), the LLM\'s output must strictly comply with a valid programming syntax or a complex JSON schema. If the model outputs syntactically invalid JSON or SQL, the downstream application crashes. What is the most robust and elegant engineering solution to guarantee 100% syntactically correct structured outputs from the LLM?',
