                correctAnswer: '`{ FIXED [Customer Name] : SUM([Sales]) }`',
                explanation: 'A **FIXED Level of Detail (LOD)** expression computes a value using only the specified dimensions, entirely independent of the dimensions in the visualization. `{ FIXED [Customer Name] : SUM([Sales]) }` calculates the absolute sum of sales for each customer across the entire dataset. Because it runs *before* standard dimension filters in Tableau\'s query pipeline, this customer total remains unchanged even if you filter the view by Year or Region, allowing you to calculate customer percentage contributions.',
