                explanation: 'With $N = 5000$ and $P = 50000$, you have the "curse of dimensionality" ($P \\gg N$). A naive model will overfit heavily on noise. The optimal pipeline is multi-stage: (1) **Variance Thresholding**: drop features that are near-constant (low variance), as they carry zero informative power; (2) **Correlation Filter**: calculate pairwise Pearson/Spearman correlations and drop highly collinear features ($|r| > 0.85$), reducing redundancy; (3) **Feature Selection (Lasso/Tree-based)**: train a model that performs feature selection (L1 Lasso or Random Forest feature importance) to select a compact subset of highly predictive features (e.g. top 200); (4) **Model Fitting**: fit the SVM on this clean, low-noise, high-value feature space. PCA is less preferred here because principal components are linear combinations of all 50,000 features, making the final model completely uninterpretable and still prone to noise aggregation.',
