                explanation: 'Minimax search explores all possible game states up to a certain depth, which grows exponentially. **Alpha-Beta Pruning** maintains two values: `alpha` (the minimum score the maximizing player is assured of) and `beta` (the maximum score the minimizing player is assured of). If at any node, the current evaluation is worse than a move the opponent already proved they can force (e.g. beta <= alpha), we "prune" (discard) the rest of that branch. It is guaranteed to return the exact same mathematical decision as a full Minimax search, but can search up to twice as deep in the same timeframe.',
