                explanation: 'Root cause: Hibernate lazy-loaded collections use proxy objects. When serialization happens, Jackson calls getters on these proxies. If the Session is closed, Hibernate cannot query the DB, raising `LazyInitializationException`. EAGER fetch globally is a major performance antipattern (leads to massive memory load). The clean solution is query-specific eager fetching (`JOIN FETCH`) or using DTOs to isolate serialization from direct persistence entities.',
